## 🔵 Reading Files

| Command | What it Does | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `cat filename` | Print contents of a file | `cat readme` |
| `cat ./` | Read a file starting with hyphen | `cat ./-` |
| `cat ./"file name"` | Read a file with spaces using quotes | `cat ./"spaces in name"` |
| `cat ./file\ name` | Read a file with spaces using backslash | `cat ./spaces\ in\ name` |
| `cat file1 file2` | Print multiple files one after another | `cat file1 file2` |

