## 🔵 Linux Dot Notation

| Symbol | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `.` | Current directory |
| `..` | Parent directory |
| `./` | "This is a file path" prefix — bypasses misinterpretation |
| `.filename` | Hidden file (starts with single dot) |
| `...filename` | Just a filename — no special meaning |

---

## 🔵 Wildcards

| Symbol | Meaning | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `*` | Match any characters | `file ./*` matches all files |
| `?` | Match single character | `file ./-file0?` matches -file00 to -file09 |

